Interview Questions & Answers
Q1. Why did you choose Regression?

Answer:
Marks are continuous numerical values, so regression is the appropriate approach instead of classification.

Q2. Why compare multiple models?

Answer:
Different algorithms perform differently on different datasets. Comparing them helps select the model with the best R² score and lowest error.

Q3. What is Train-Test Split?

Answer:
The dataset is divided into training and testing sets. The model learns from the training data and is evaluated on unseen testing data.

Q4. What is R² Score?

Answer:
R² measures how well the model explains the variance in the target variable. A value closer to 1 indicates a better fit.

Q5. Why save the model?

Answer:
Saving the trained model allows reuse for predictions without retraining every time, reducing computation time.
